message.text:
The “Evangelion and Japanese Swords” Exhibition WEEK! Updates on the exhibit and related info will be up EVERYDAY this week:)
「ヱヴァンゲリヲンと日本刀」展、パリにて絶賛公開中！今週はパリ展の様子＆関連情報について“毎日”投稿！
＜　http://www.jpf.go.jp/e/culture/new/1401/01-01.html　＞

Day3：At the exhibit in Paris, visitors enjoy reading the cutline of Japanese swords, which explains a history and types of Japanese swords as well as its making process in detail. 
So here is a QUIZ! Japanese sword consists of beautiful parts or pieces to make it as a great art. One of the Japanese swords’ significant beauty is called “Hamon （刃文,はもん）”　which is different depending on the era or styles of swordsmith. 
Ｑ：Which part is called “Hamon” in the picture?

パリ展では、日本刀の種類や部位、刀ができるまでの工程を詳しく説明した文章に、みんな興味深々！
ここでクイズ！日本刀はそれぞれの美しいパーツが集まってひとつの芸術になりますが、日本刀の美しさのひとつとしてあげられる、時代や流派によって異なる「刃文（はもん）」と呼ばれる部分はどこ？

message.text:
The “Evangelion and Japanese Swords” Exhibition WEEK! Updates on the exhibit and related info will be up EVERYDAY this week:)
「ヱヴァンゲリヲンと日本刀」展、パリにて絶賛公開中！今週はパリ展の様子＆関連情報について“毎日”投稿！
＜　http://www.jpf.go.jp/e/culture/new/1401/01-01.html　＞
 　　 
Many people from all ages have come to the exhibit in Paris, and they are giving us positive feedback like “Very beautiful exhibit”&“Detailed cutline is impressive” etc…!!!
A lot of visitors seem to stay at the venue quite long, which shows how much it could attract them. 
Hope the exhibit will convey the visitors the universal sophistication and beauty of Japanese arts in old and modern ages through this collaboration.
<<What kind of collaboration would you like to see using Japanese traditional art and Japanese animation??>> 

パリ展では、若い方から年配のお客様、ファミリーでいらっしゃる方々など、幅広い層のお客様に足を運んでいただいています。フランス人のお客様からは、「美しい展示」「詳しい解説が面白い」といった声が。長い時間鑑賞してくださるお客様が多いのも、本展の特徴です。
時代が違ってもなお、伝統と現代に共通して息づく日本の芸術の精緻さ・美しさ。フランスの方々にも伝わったでしょうか。
【あなたなら、どんな日本の伝統文化とアニメのコラボがみてみたいですか：）？】
